{"履修期": "秋学期前半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course is neither a lecture series nor is it an academic study. Although the syllabus is set, students will lead the lessons, while the instructional staff will be available for assistance and monitoring of English-language progress.", "到達目標": "The communication goals of this course are: 1.) to guide students in mastering formulaic language that both increases oral fluency and is essential to survival in an English-speaking office environment. 2.) to guide students in developing top-down and bottom- up listening that is essential to survival in an English-speaking office environment.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">English Communication; Business Communication</span></span></span></span>", "授業の概要・背景": "<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Business Communication will be a weekly, 100-minute course designed to increase students' Business English output and interaction through the use of specific skill-instruction: oral communication and email writing. These are the two most relevant skills to your English communication in the modern workplace.</span></span></span></span>", "授業方法": "Face-to-face format. Discussions/pair work/group activities: Students will be required to log and study new vocabulary on their own: specifically, vocab that arises in the event of a breakdown in student-to-student communication. Discussions/ pair work/group activities: Students will be required to work together to complete their email-writing workbooks. Lectures: guidance from the instructor will come at the end of class, to clarify lessons targets/answer questions that students may have.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-alig